<paragraph id="8BDB4242FFB2FFF227D9FEABE5A9FD99" blockId="6.[151,1437,223,538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF227D9FEABE720FEC1" bold="true" box="[199,273,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Notes.</emphasis>
The species was found in a small area in the immediate vicinity of a wine-growing region. The warmthfavoured site was characterized by small bushes and dry, unimproved grassland. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6439C1FFB2FFF2232BFEC0E2F2FEE5" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1077,1219,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moenium">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF2232BFEC0E2F2FEE5" box="[1077,1219,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">M. moenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the three cryptic species within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6439C1FFB2FFF226A3FEE3E442FE09" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[445,627,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF226A3FEE3E442FE09" box="[445,627,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Merodon avidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, which can be found in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF53FB3FFB2FFF22354FEE3E31DFE0A" author="Popovic, D. &amp; Acanski, J. &amp; Djan, M. &amp; Obreht, D. &amp; Vujic, A. &amp; Radenkovic, S." box="[1098,1324,367,394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="790 - 809" refId="ref21107" refString="Popovic, D., Acanski, J., Djan, M., Obreht, D., Vujic, A. &amp; Radenkovic, S. (2015) Sibling species delimitation and nomenclature of the Merodon avidus complex (Diptera Syrphidae). European Journal of Entomology, 112, 790 - 809. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2015.100" type="journal article" year="2015">
Popović 
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF223B1FEFCE2D0FE09" box="[1199,1249,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Only 
<taxonomicName id="4C6439C1FFB2FFF22260FEFCE6D1FE2D" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF22260FEFCE6D1FE2D" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">M. avidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="4C6439C1FFB2FFF22603FE18E79AFE2D" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[285,427,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moenium">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF22603FE18E79AFE2D" box="[285,427,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">M. moenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in 
<collectingCountry id="F37302D2FFB2FFF22507FE1FE45FFE2D" box="[537,622,403,429]" name="Austria" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Austria</collectingCountry>
, respectively in Central Europe. The third species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6439C1FFB2FFF223A2FE18E30FFE2D" authorityName="Vujic" authorityYear="2015" box="[1212,1342,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibericus">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF223A2FE18E2E2FE2D" box="[1212,1235,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF223FAFE1FE30FFE2D" box="[1252,1342,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">ibericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is only recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F37302D2FFB2FFF22621FE3BE7B3FE51" box="[319,386,439,465]" name="Spain" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37302D2FFB2FFF22693FE3BE7DDFE51" box="[397,492,439,465]" name="Portugal" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Portugal</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F37302D2FFB2FFF2253AFE34E4B8FE52" box="[548,649,440,466]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF53FB3FFB2FFF22586FE3BE505FE51" author="Speight, M. C. D." box="[664,820,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" refId="ref22192" refString="Speight, M. C. D. (2020) Species accounts of European Syrphidae, 2020. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera). Vol. 104. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin, 314 pp." type="book" year="2020">Speight 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Due to the similarity of external morphological characteristics, it must be assumed that most of the older records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6439C1FFB2FFF2247FFE50E5FEFE75" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[865,975,475,502]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF2247FFE50E549FE75" box="[865,888,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF22498FE57E5FEFE75" box="[902,975,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">avidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the published literature probably refer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6439C1FFB2FFF227AAFD8CE771FD99" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[180,320,512,538]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moenium">
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF227AAFD8CE6FAFD99" box="[180,203,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9109E50FFB2FFF227C7FD8CE771FD99" box="[217,320,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">moenium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, previous records need to be re-examined.
</paragraph>
